   <TEXT>
   <S PAR='1' RSNT='1' SNO='1'>LESSON TWENTY-FIVE HUMAN UNCLEANNESS</S>
   <S PAR='2' RSNT='1' SNO='2'>HUMAN BIRTH, LEPROSY, AND DISCHARGES OUTLINE Human birth: Woman s relationship to human birth: Woman representing all mankind.</S>
   <S PAR='3' RSNT='1' SNO='3'>The human birth coming out of the woman being unclean.</S>
   <S PAR='4' RSNT='1' SNO='4'>The uncleanness of the male s birth.</S>
   <S PAR='5' RSNT='1' SNO='5'>The uncleanness of the female s birth.</S>
   <S PAR='6' RSNT='1' SNO='6'>The way for man to be cleansed from human uncleanness: Being circumcised: The cutting off of man s natural being.</S>
   <S PAR='7' RSNT='1' SNO='7'>Carried out on the eighth day.</S>
   <S PAR='8' RSNT='1' SNO='8'>Offering Christ as the burnt offering and the sin offering: The burnt offering.</S>
   <S PAR='9' RSNT='1' SNO='9'>The sin offering.</S>
   <S PAR='10' RSNT='1' SNO='10'>Leprosy: The origin of leprosy.</S>
   <S PAR='11' RSNT='1' SNO='11'>The nature of leprosy.</S>
   <S PAR='12' RSNT='1' SNO='12'>The result of leprosy.</S>
   <S PAR='13' RSNT='1' SNO='13'>Leprosy signifying the sin that dwells in man.</S>
   <S PAR='14' RSNT='1' SNO='14'>The leper: Tearing his clothes, having his hair let loose, and covering his upper lip and crying Unclean, unclean!</S>
   <S PAR='15' RSNT='1' SNO='15'>Dwelling alone outside the camp.</S>
   <S PAR='16' RSNT='1' SNO='16'>Discharges: All discharges from the human body being unclean.</S>
   <S PAR='17' RSNT='1' SNO='17'>The way for cleansing a person who has a discharge: Washing the clothes and bathing the body in running water.</S>
   <S PAR='18' RSNT='1' SNO='18'>Offering a sin offering and a burnt offering on the eighth day.</S>
   </TEXT>
